data.description: Beautifully situated in the heart of Long Beach, this charming home at 2550 Old Zaferia Way offers a wonderful opportunity for a family looking to settle into a cozy abode with room for personalization. Boasting a single ownership spanning 27 years, this residence is graciously maintained, promising a warm and inviting atmosphere.    Featuring 3 bedrooms and 3 bathrooms spread across a spacious 1,530 square feet, this 1991-built gem exudes comfort and functionality. The potential for customization is abundant, with opportunities to enhance the interior with fresh carpets and a new coat of paint, allowing for personal touches that will truly make this house a home.    Nestled within a quaint gated community, residents will enjoy both privacy and security. Its central location offers unparalleled convenience, with Long Beach State University, the Long Beach Airport, and a plethora of dining options and freeway access just minutes away.    With its desirable location, ample space, and potential for customization, this home presents an exceptional opportunity for those seeking a cozy yet customizable living experience in Long Beach, California.
